⚠️ ✅ 2. Model Risk
👉 What it means:

The risk that a model is wrong, misused, or misunderstood, leading to bad decisions.


✅ Types of model risk:


Data issues

Poor quality or biased data



Model errors

Incorrect assumptions
Overfitting



Misuse

Using model outside intended purpose



Bias / fairness issues

Unintended discrimination




✅ In pricing:

Underpricing → losses
Overpricing → lost customers / fairness issues


🎯 What “strong grasp” means:
You can:

Identify risks
Mitigate them
Explain and justify models


🔄 ✅ 3. Change Control
👉 What it means:

A structured process to manage changes to models or pricing rules safely


✅ Why this is needed:
Even small changes can:

Impact profitability
Break compliance
Introduce bias


✅ In practice:
When a model is updated:

Document changes
Revalidate model
Get approvals
Track version history
Deploy safely


📌 Example:

Updating a GLM coefficient:

Must go through approval process
Cannot just “push to production”




